President Cyril Ramaphosa will on Sunday participate in the 12-kilometre fun walk that forms part of the 33rd annual fundraiser Gandhi Walk in Lenasia, the presidency said.
The event is organised to promote community and health awareness, and this year’s theme is ‘Going Green’ to draw attention to climate change and the need to protect the environment.
The walk will start and end at the Ghandi Hall in Lenasia.
– African News Agency (ANA)
